Let $z = 2 + \sqrt{2} - (3 + 3 \sqrt{2})i$, and let $c = 2 - 3i$.  Let $w$ be the result when $z$ is rotated around $c$ by $\frac{\pi}{4}$ counter-clockwise.

[asy]
unitsize(0.6 cm);

pair C, W, Z;

Z = (2 + sqrt(2), -3 - 3*sqrt(2));
C = (2,-3);
W = rotate(45,C)*(Z);

draw(Z--C--W);

dot("$c$", C, N);
dot("$w$", W, SE);
dot("$z$", Z, S);
label("$\frac{\pi}{4}$", C + (0.6,-1));
[/asy]

Find $w.$

Proposed Solution:
Let w be z rotated about c by π/4 counterclockwise. Then
w = c + e^{iπ/4}(z − c).

Compute z − c:
z − c = (2 + √2) − (3 + 3√2)i − (2 − 3i)
      = √2 − 3√2 i
      = √2(1 − 3i).

Since e^{iπ/4} = (√2/2)(1 + i),
w − c = e^{iπ/4}(z − c) = (√2/2)(1 + i) · √2(1 − 3i)
      = (1 + i)(1 − 3i)
      = 4 − 2i.

Thus w = c + (4 − 2i) = (2 − 3i) + (4 − 2i) = 6 − 5i.

\boxed{6 - 5i}

